Thomas J. Johnston
Of San Francisco
Who visited these gardens as a commander in the U.S. Navy
During the Normandy Landings and Later with his family
and as president of his company"»
≈In memory of
Dr Thomas Schofield
who worked in Queen Square from 2004-2010
All of old. Nothing else ever. Ever tried. Ever failed
No matter. Try again. Fail again
Fail better
(Samuel Beckett)"À
»Svetlana Grigorlan
13.08.1950 - 13.03.2019
If roses grew in Heaven, Lord please pick a bunch for me, place them in my
Mother's arms and tell her they're from me. Tell her I love her and miss her,
and when she turns smile, place a kiss upon her cheek and hold her for a while.
In loving memory of mum and wife that meant so much."Ã
